The President, Muhammadu Buhari on Monday May 13, hosted the Governor of the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN), Godwin Emefiele at the presidential villa in Abuja. Emefiele, all smiles, shook hands with President Buhari who congratulated him over his recent re-appointment at the governor of the apex bank. THEWILL recalls that President Buhari, last week nominated Emefiele for a second term in office and forwarded his name to the Senate for confirmation. Emefiele was first appointed by former President Goodluck Jonathan in 2014 and was retained after Buhari assumed office in 2015. With this reappointment, Emefiele is now the last man standing from the former president, Goodluck Jonathanâ€™s administration